  "text": "Methods for improving energy efficiency of cluster devices can be roughly divided into three categories: workload shaping, users' behavior shaping, and resource adjustment. Workload shaping is widely used in network devices. Its idea is to use a proxy between a service and a user that changes the incoming traffic through buffering to enable longer sleep times for some continuous period of time and on the other hand longer periods of high utilization [CITATION_1] . Shaping users' behavior is well tried in electrical power companies, in which the price of electricity is usually cheaper during low workload activity periods e.g. nights. This encourages forcing users to use electricity at least partly during the night time leading to the smoother workload. A problem with these methods is that they easily reduce quality of service for users.",
